title: Print, "Two designs for candy boxes", 1780–90
provenance: From the Collection of Léon Decloux
creditline: Purchased for the Museum by the Advisory Council
description: Fan shaped portions.  The design at left shows two ovoidal medallians with females busts.  The one at right shows an open ovoidal medallion.  Fluting and moulding at centers, moulding at edges

tombstone.epitaph:
Print, "Two designs for candy boxes", 1780–90.
1780–90. Etching on paper. Purchased for the Museum by the Advisory Council. 1921-6-18.
